de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.model.morphology
Class RelatedForm

java.lang.Object
  de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.model.morphology.RelatedForm
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<RelatedForm>
public class RelatedForm
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<RelatedForm>

RelatedForm is a class representing a word form or a morph that can be related to the LexicalEntry in one of a variety of ways (e.g. derivation, root).

Author:
Zijad Maksuti

getFormRepresentations

public java.util.List<FormRepresentation> getFormRepresentations()
Returns the List of all FormRepresentation instances of the Lemma associated to the LexicalEntry targeted by the relation represented by this RelatedForm instance.

Returns:
the list of all form representations of the lemma associated to the lexical entry targeted by this related form.
If the targeted lexical entry's lemma does not have any form representations, this method should return an empty list.
See Also:
getTargetLexicalEntry(), setFormRepresentations(List)
